<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="919" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d919">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10052:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-17T20:00:00+02:00">April 17, 1941—8
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 17—5:26 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1479. The German Ambassador to Turkey Von Papen is reported to have
                                left Ankara for Istanbul on his way to Berlin. A source which has
                                wide connections in official circles says this means the first step
                                in endeavoring to force the Turkish Government to come to terms and
                                that high official circles are confident of succeeding as a result
                                of the altered military and strategic situation in the Near
                                East.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>